            "answer_text": "No. They're extremely quiet. But that's because there's no sound in space. Sound is a form of energy. And stars have plenty of energy. The problem is that this energy is not converted to sound energy at all. It's in the form heat and light. If 100% of this energy is converted to sound( I assume that the universe somehow gets a medium through which sound can easily travel) then that sound would be extremely loud. It would be beyond words. And if all of this sound from the star(let it be our sun) travels towards the earth, the earth would shake violently, crack, break up into several pieces and those pieces would fly out of the solar system. But I will handle everything if this happens. I have a plan and I will survive. ",
